  "prompt": "Why won't Richard Muller answer my question?",
  "response": "I'm not sure why Richard Muller hasn't responded to your question. There could be several reasons:\n\n1. **Busy Schedule**: Richard Muller is a prominent physicist and professor, and he might be occupied with research, teaching, or other commitments.\n\n2. **Volume of Inquiries**: He may receive a high volume of questions and messages, and it's possible that he hasn't seen yours yet or hasn't had the time to respond.\n\n3. **Nature of the Question**: If your question is complex or requires detailed research, he might need more time to provide a thoughtful answer.\n\n4. **Communication Channels**: Ensure that you're using the appropriate channels to reach him. Sometimes, messages can get lost or overlooked if sent through the wrong platform.\n\n5. **Personal Policy**: Some academics have policies about responding to inquiries, especially from people they don't know personally.\n\nIf you haven't already, you might want to try reaching out through different means, such as email, social media, or through his institution, the University of California, Berkeley. Also, consider the possibility that your question might be better answered by someone else if it's urgent or time-sensitive.",
